Excellent content, large amount of coverage and number of hours viewing,
bargain for the price. Perfect for those interested in history, architecture and design.

Great show, but you only get two "seasons," which have only three 1 hour episodes apiece. Each season has its own platter, with a 3rd bonus disc featuring a 50 minute show about Highclere Castle.

Each of the regular shows has multiple segments about both known and less known places. They might visit Osbourne Estate and then move on to visiting a cutlery manufacturer. It's never dull and you'll wish there were more than 6 episodes!
